name: dfs.blockreport.incremental.intervalMsec
description:
If set to a positive integer, the value in ms to wait between sending
    incremental block reports from the Datanode to the Namenode.

name: dfs.client.block.write.locateFollowingBlock.max.delay.ms
description: The maximum delay (unit is ms) before retrying locateFollowingBlock.

name: hadoop.zk.retry-interval-ms
description: Retry interval in milliseconds when connecting to ZooKeeper.

name: dfs.blockreport.split.threshold
description:
If the number of blocks on the DataNode is below this
    threshold then it will send block reports for all Storage Directories
    in a single message.

    If the number of blocks exceeds this threshold then the DataNode will
    send block reports for each Storage Directory in separate messages.

    Set to zero to always split.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.suspectnode.interval.ms
description: Interval time in milliseconds for probing suspect node behavior.

name: fs.s3a.paging.maximum
description:
How many keys to request from S3 when doing
     directory listings at a time.
